reviews.text: Beers were good. Tried to enjoy a promotion that they posted online, but no one knew anything about it. Tried to order off the set lunch menu, but they didn't have half of the dishes. Very underwhelming experience.
Enjoyed the beer and skewer platter combo.  Nice food, and beer!  The platter allows u to try different types of beer in a row.  A little bit pricey, but worth a try!

Used to love this place but seems that they have changed the owner or at least most of the staff. Food is still delicious, and outdoor seating is still nice, but without the friendly service one might want to think twice before paying this price for a beer.

Great spot for beers & yakitori style food
Team hospitality is top notch also
Has a outdoor spot which is icing on the cake

Average service, average food, average beer. Champagne prices with beer tastes. Very weak. Disappointing after specifically selecting this place for the Yakatori. They should call it skewered averagness!

result.name: Coedo Taproom

reviews.text:
發現係銅鑼灣Fashion Walk有間以COEDO手工啤酒
為主既串燒概念店，聽講好多菜式都係由日藉廚師
主理，包括一系列自家製埼玉縣既地道風味，
唔同類型既午市定食，由沙律、丼飯同埋串燒迎合
返唔同香港人既口味。黎緊8月1號開始晏就時間
12-4點仲會推出Semi-lunch buffet呀，夠哂"咀雕"既
我到時要趁Lunchtime過黎chill下，遠離一下煩囂啦！👇
-
📌 Eel Stone Pot Rice - $118
👉 原條燒鰻魚，貨真價實，望落都覺得夠哂肥美，
又夠光漣，質感都唔錯，師傅控制火侯夠準確，
以石鍋呈上一般效果會更加濃香，飯焦佈滿哂
成個鍋底，撈埋醬汁一齊食真係絕頂呀！
-
📌 Trio Bento - $108
▪ Lightly Grilled Salmon Salad 
▪ Grilled Ginger Pork 
▪ Salted Grilled Mackerel
👉 三色便當分別由炙燒三文魚沙律、生薑燒豚肉
同埋鹽燒鯖魚既和式料理，配埋白飯，多種層次混合
一齊好特別，最出色要大讚既一定係鯖魚同炙燒三文魚，
兩者都燒得夠香，外面亦做到好香脆，
沙律亦都好新鮮，食得過！
-
📌Kushiyaki/Skewer
▪ Chicken Heart - $40/string
▪ Chicken Wings- $42/string
▫ 餐廳既自家製串燒係用備長炭高溫烤製，
用料絕對唔馬虎，特登嗌左兩款串燒黎送酒，
惹味之餘，衝擊口味蕾既層次，兩個字：爽呀！
-
▪ Beniaka  - (+$10)/S Size
▪ Shikkoku - (+$10)/S Size
▫ Lunchtime黎整杯手工啤特別寫意呀！
餐廳既手工啤賣點係百分百以麥芽釀製，
標榜無添加任造人造防腐劑同添加劑，接近天然，
品種亦多，今次試左兩隻，分別以唔同啤酒象徵
日本傳統顏色，Beniaka就代表"紅赤"，
Shikkoku就代表"漆黑"，兩者入口有種淡香，
濃郁既麥味，配埋串燒無得彈呀！

Beers were good. Tried to enjoy a promotion that they posted online, but no one knew anything about it. Tried to order off the set lunch menu, but they didn't have half of the dishes. Very underwhelming experience.
Enjoyed the beer and skewer platter combo.  Nice food, and beer!  The platter allows u to try different types of beer in a row.  A little bit pricey, but worth a try!

Used to love this place but seems that they have changed the owner or at least most of the staff. Food is still delicious, and outdoor seating is still nice, but without the friendly service one might want to think twice before paying this price for a beer.

Great spot for beers & yakitori style food
Team hospitality is top notch also
Has a outdoor spot which is icing on the cake
